results.occurrenceRemarks: Medium-large flock (several hundred) light-brown ducks with white faces (whistling teal by their calls) on the eastern shore of the River Niger. As we approached by boat from the north they became nervous, standing up, and then flying out into the river, where they landed forming a large shoal of gently bobbing ducks.
